The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 05 December is 9,491 (1,098.5 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 30 November, there were 487 new confirmed cases (56.4 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 23 November, there were 660 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 26% (173 fewer cases).
